# Debugging sstate with diffsigs

## The problem

Your build is using the wrong sstate cache. Or worse — rebuilding everything.

## The fix

```bash
# Find task signatures
bitbake -S printdiff <recipe>

# Compare two signatures
bitbake-diffsigs <sig1> <sig2>

# Human-readable diff
bitbake-diffsigs -t <recipe> do_compile
```

## Real example

```bash
$ bitbake-diffsigs tmp/stamps/*/mydriver/do_compile.sigdata.*
basehash changed from 8e7b9a3c to 4d2f1e6b
Variable do_compile value changed:
  -${MAKE} modules
  +${MAKE} modules -j4
```

## Common causes

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---------|-------------|-----|
| Hash mismatch | Variable changed in conf | Check local.conf overrides |
| Missing sstate | DEPENDS changed | Audit recipe dependencies |
| Random rebuilds | Timestamps in task | Remove date from do_compile |

## Pro tip

```bash
# See what's influencing a task's hash
bitbake -e <recipe> | grep -A5 -B5 "BB_BASEHASH_<task>"
```
```

