# OTA updates with RAUC and Mender

## RAUC (Robust Auto-Update Controller)

**Best for:** Industrial, medical, automotive

### Setup

```bitbake
# local.conf
IMAGE_INSTALL:append = " rauc"
RAUC_BUNDLE_SLOTS = "rootfs.0 rootfs.1"
RAUC_KEY_FILE = "${TOPDIR}/keys/development-1.key"
RAUC_CERT_FILE = "${TOPDIR}/keys/development-1.cert"
```

### Create update bundle

```bash
rauc bundle --key=dev.key --cert=dev.cert --manifest=manifest.raucm update.raucb
```

### Deploy

```bash
scp update.raucb target:/tmp/
ssh target "rauc install /tmp/update.raucb"
```

## Mender

**Best for:** IoT devices, fleets

### Setup

```bitbake
# local.conf
INHERIT += "mender-full"
MENDER_ARTIFACT_NAME = "release-2.0"
MENDER_SERVER_URL = "https://mender.example.com"
```

### Create artifact

```bash
mender-artifact write rootfs-image -n release-2.0 -f core-image-full-cmdline.sdimg -o release-2.0.mender
```

### Deploy via server

```bash
curl -X POST https://mender.example.com/api/devices/v1/artifacts \
  -F artifact=@release-2.0.mender
```

## Comparison

| Feature | RAUC | Mender |
|---------|------|--------|
| Complexity | Medium | High |
| Server required | No | Yes (optional) |
| Rollback | Yes | Yes |
| A/B partitions | Required | Optional |
| Bandwidth | Low | Medium |
| Best for | Industrial | IoT fleets |

## Failure recovery

**RAUC:**
```bash
rauc status
rauc install --force bundle.raucb  # Force reinstall
```

**Mender:**
```bash
mender -show-artifact
mender -commit  # Confirm update
mender -rollback
```
```

