# Performance: ccache + sstate mirrors

## ccache (compiler cache)

**30-70% rebuild speedup**

### Setup

```bitbake
# local.conf
CCACHE = "ccache"
CCACHE_DIR = "${TOPDIR}/ccache"
INHERIT += "ccache"
```

### Monitor

```bash
ccache -s
# Cache hits: 245 / 300 (81%)
```

## sstate mirrors

**Share cache across CI runners**

### Local mirror

```bitbake
# local.conf
SSTATE_DIR = "${TOPDIR}/sstate-cache"
SSTATE_MIRRORS = "file://.* file:///mnt/nas/sstate/PATH"
```

### HTTP mirror

```bitbake
SSTATE_MIRRORS = "file://.* http://build-cache.company.com/sstate/PATH"
```

### Push to mirror

```bash
bitbake <target> --runonly=fetch
bitbake <target> -S none
rsync -av tmp/sstate-control/ user@cache-server:/sstate/
```

## Optimize both

```bitbake
# Combined optimization
BB_NUMBER_THREADS = "8"
PARALLEL_MAKE = "-j 8"
CCACHE = "ccache"
SSTATE_MIRRORS = "file://.* http://fast-cache.local/sstate/"
```

## Metrics comparison

| Configuration | Build time | Cache hit % |
|--------------|------------|-------------|
| No cache | 45 min | 0% |
| ccache only | 32 min | 35% |
| sstate only | 18 min | 60% |
| Both | 12 min | 85% |
```

