# Distributed builds with distcc

## Setup distcc cluster

### On build host (client)

```bitbake
# local.conf
DISTCC = "distcc"
DISTCC_DIR = "${TOPDIR}/distcc"
INHERIT += "distcc"
PARALLEL_MAKE = "-j 16"
DISTCC_HOSTS = "192.168.1.10 192.168.1.11 192.168.1.12"
```

### On compile servers

```bash
# Install distccd
apt install distcc
# Configure
echo "192.168.1.0/24" >> /etc/distcc/clients.allow
systemctl start distccd
```

## Monitor

```bash
distccmon-text 2  # Update every 2 seconds
```

## Icecream (alternative)

**Better for heterogeneous clusters**

```bitbake
INHERIT += "icecc"
ICECC_CC = "gcc"
ICECC_CXX = "g++"
```

## Performance

| Build type | Time | Speedup |
|------------|------|---------|
| Local (8 cores) | 30 min | 1x |
| 3 distcc hosts | 12 min | 2.5x |
| 8 distcc hosts | 8 min | 3.75x |

## Caveats

- Network latency affects small files
- Not all tasks can distribute
- Toolchain must match across hosts
