# Systemd & Boot Integration Interview Prep

## Systemd in Yocto

**Enable systemd:**
```bitbake
INIT_MANAGER = "systemd"
DISTRO_FEATURES:append = " systemd"
```

**Add custom service:**
```bitbake
inherit systemd
SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = "myservice.service"
SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE:${PN} = "enable"
```

## Common questions

**Q1: Systemd vs SysV init?**
- Parallel boot
- On-demand daemons
- cgroup resource mgmt
- journald logging

**Q2: Debug a failing unit**
```bash
systemctl status myservice
journalctl -u myservice -f
strace -p $(pidof myservice)
```

**Q3: Make service wait for network**
```ini
[Unit]
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/myapp

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

**Q4: Resource limits**
```ini
[Service]
CPUQuota=50%
MemoryMax=100M
TasksMax=20
```

**Q5: Boot optimization**
```bash
systemd-analyze blame
systemd-analyze critical-chain
systemctl mask unnecessary-service
```

## Production patterns

**Watchdog:**
```ini
[Service]
WatchdogSec=30s
Restart=always
```

**Read-only rootfs:**
```bash
# systemd will write to /var, /tmp, /run
mount -o remount,ro /
```

**Journal to RAM:**
```bash
mkdir /var/log/journal
systemd-tmpfiles --create --prefix /var/log/journal
```
